snippet.textDisplay:
My daughter does cheer for her basketball team and has been asked to join next years basketball team back in December before Christmas break I was thinking to myself what a wonderful opportunity to introduce her to greatness (Kobe)

The day of the tragedy I was in my kitchen when my daughter told me that Kobe had died I took to the desk top and could not believe what I was discovering, I was in shock... I’m from California but have lived in Vegas for several years I am Cali to the fullest, I grew up on snoop dog and was memorized by Vanessa when the G’z up music video dropped I was obsessed with the Eric sermons LA Lakers Anthem, everyone I went to school with middle and the threw out high school was INSPIRED by Kobe, he was legend. Kobe retired then came out of retirement he has made a beautiful family and rose above the occasion to bring honor to his family even after main stream media took flight to destroy his legacy, I had forgot about the alleged scandal and even when it was prevalent I disregarded it and after the fact had always admired Kobe and Vanessa’s resiliency to endure the trials they faced and celebrated when they prevailed and chose to stay together, proud of the man he became after he stepped off the court, they have a beautiful family and gorgeous children, as a parent I felt the immediate drop of the heart when I had learned his child also to had perished I prayed being unfaultered the whole day for their strength to endure the sting of death, I watched the live board cast of family who went to the staples center to show support I too being their in spirit to grasp reality like many others who were in California that knew no where else to go, I never focused on the crash it’s self I just kept thinking of Gianna and how Kobe’s heart felt as a parent... towards sunset I came out of my house to my porch and looked up at the sky the clouds rolled in from California over Las Vegas and I sat there and looked at them they look very different from any clouds I’ve seen they had a divine essence about them and with an hour once the sun had set i was visited by them I was stunned for what I seen for a split second was them in halos that were neon blue And to my eyes what I was only able to see was the halos and the height of the halos were precisely the height of Kobe and Gianna standing side by side across from me at that moment I knew they made it to the promise land And shortly after the clouds had rolled in cleared out🙏🏾❤️ I pray for us you are still mourning to have peace and to just believe they are together in a better place for this world is just for a moment and the hardest part is not that they left but we are left behind, I choose to be inspired and to celebrate their life and thank G-d for the time we had together ❤️ may G-d bless all who were onboard and perished, salvation is theirs ❤️
